- **Desktop and Responsive Form/Grid/Table Layout Standards**
  - Use `max-w-5xl mx-auto p-4` for main container width and centering.
  - Use `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2` or `md:grid-cols-3` for responsive column layout.
  - Use `gap-6` or `gap-8` for consistent spacing between fields/sections.
  - Use `bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-6` for form and card containers.
  - For summary+thumbnail + form, use `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3` and place summary in `md:col-span-1`, form in `md:col-span-2`.
  - On mobile, summary and form stack vertically; on desktop, they are side-by-side.

- **Button and Icon Standards**
  - Use Tailwind classes: `bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded hover:bg-blue-700 font-semibold` for primary actions.
  - For icon buttons, use `.icon-btn`, `.icon-btn-edit`, `.icon-btn-delete`, `.icon-btn-upload` (see `src/app/globals.css`).
  - Example:
    ```tsx
    <button className="icon-btn icon-btn-edit"><FaEdit /></button>
    <button className="bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded hover:bg-blue-700 font-semibold">Register</button>
    ```

- **Checkbox and Grid/Table UI**
  - Use `.custom-checkbox` and `.custom-checkbox-tick` for all checkboxes.
  - Use `.custom-grid-table` and `.custom-grid-cell` for grid/table layouts in forms and admin UIs.
  - See `src/app/globals.css` for implementation.

- **Responsive Design**
  - Always use Tailwind responsive classes (`md:`, `lg:`) to ensure forms and tables adapt to screen size.
  - For event registration and media forms, summary+thumbnail is above the form on mobile, side-by-side on desktop.

- **Consistent Use of Tailwind Utility Classes**
  - Use Tailwind for spacing (`p-2`, `p-4`, `mb-4`), sizing (`w-full`, `max-w-xl`), color (`bg-gray-50`, `text-gray-700`), and border (`rounded`, `border`).
  - Avoid inline styles except for rare cases (e.g., hero image overlays).

- **References**
  - See `src/app/globals.css` for custom classes and utility patterns.
  - See `src/components/ProfileForm.tsx` and `src/app/admin/events/[id]/media/MediaClientPage.tsx` for best-practice form and grid layouts.
  - See `src/app/events/[id]/register/page.tsx` for public-facing form implementation.

- **Rationale**
  - Ensures modern, accessible, visually consistent forms and admin UIs.
  - Reduces design drift and improves maintainability.
  - Makes onboarding and cross-team work easier.

